# Client Financial Dashboard

## Purpose

Provide an at-a-glance financial summary of the client account without requiring users to review invoices, payments, or statements individually.

The dashboard should appear at the top of the Client Billing Workspace and serve as the primary financial overview for the client.

---

## Dashboard KPIs

### Revenue Metrics

| Metric                | Description                          |
| --------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
| Total Quoted          | Total value of all quotations issued |
| Total Invoiced        | Total value of all invoices issued   |
| Total Paid            | Total payments received              |
| Outstanding Balance   | Amount still owed                    |
| Overdue Balance       | Total overdue amount                 |
| Average Invoice Value | Average invoice amount               |
| Largest Invoice       | Largest invoice issued               |

---

## Invoice Metrics

| Metric           | Description                       |
| ---------------- | --------------------------------- |
| Total Invoices   | Number of invoices created        |
| Draft Invoices   | Number of draft invoices          |
| Sent Invoices    | Number of sent invoices           |
| Paid Invoices    | Number of fully paid invoices     |
| Partially Paid   | Number of partially paid invoices |
| Overdue Invoices | Number of overdue invoices        |

---

## Quotation Metrics

| Metric              | Description                           |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| Total Quotations    | Number of quotations issued           |
| Draft Quotations    | Number of draft quotations            |
| Accepted Quotations | Number accepted                       |
| Rejected Quotations | Number rejected                       |
| Expired Quotations  | Number expired                        |
| Conversion Rate     | Accepted quotes converted to invoices |

